nia)|Airplay 100]])<!--Please do not change this to Romanian Top 100 or Media Forest. The Airplay 100 is Romania's national singles chart from 2012 onwards. For further information, see WP:GOODCHARTS--><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kissfm.ro/podcasturi/6842|title=Airplay 100 \u2013 15 martie 2020|publisher=[[Kiss FM (Romania)|Kiss FM]]|language=Romanian|accessdate=March 26, 2020|date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n| 98\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Singapore ([[Recording Industry Association (Singapore)|RIAS]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rias.org.sg/rias-top-charts/|title=RIAS International Top Charts Week 15|publisher=Recording Industry Association (Singapore)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200417101348/https://www.rias.org.sg/rias-top-charts/|archive-date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| 14\n|-\n{{single chart|Slovakdigital|14|year=2020|week=15|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Sweden ([[Sverigetopplistan]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sverigetopplistan.se/chart/41?dspy=2020&dspp=15|title=Veckolista Singlar, vecka 15|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n| 22\n|-\n{{single chart|Switzerland|30|artist=Lil Mosey|song=Blueberry Faygo|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 13, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|UK|9|date=20200417|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 18, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardhot100|18|artist=Lil Mosey|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrandbhiphop|10|artist=Lil Mosey|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardrhythmic|12|artist=Lil Mosey|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 14, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 100|''Rolling Stone'' Top 100]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/songs/2020-03-13/|title=Top 100 Songs|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref>\n| 21\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Country\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| February 7, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Interscope Records|Interscope]]\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"DX\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|United States\n| March 10, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Rhythmic contemporary|Rhythmic contemporary radio]]}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref name=\"us-rh-radio\">{{cite web |title=Top 40 Rhythmic Future Releases |url=https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases |website=All Access Music Group |accessdate=March 9, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309160408/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-rhythmic/future-releases |archivedate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Lil Mosey}}\n\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:Lil Mosey songs]]\n[[Category:Interscope Records singles]]\n[[Category:TikTok songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 single by Lil Mosey}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Blueberry Faygo\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Lil Mosey - Blueberry Faygo.png\n| artist     = [[Lil Mosey]]\n| album      = [[Certified Hitmaker|Certified Hitmaker (reissue)]]\n| released   = {{start date|2020|2|7|mf=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| genre      =\n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=43}}\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Interscope Records|Interscope]]|Mogul Vision}}\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Lil Mosey|Lathan Echols]]|[[Johnny Gill|Johnny Gill, Jr.]]|[[L.A. Reid|Antonio Reid]]|[[Babyface (musician)|Kenneth Edmonds]]|Callan Wong}}\n| producer   = Callan\n| chronology = [[Lil Mosey]]\n| prev_title = [[Stuck in a Dream]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| title      = Blueberry Faygo\n| year       = 2020\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|V_jHc_n0p9c|\"Blueberry Faygo\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Blueberry Faygo'''\" is a single by American rapper [[Lil Mosey]]. It was released on February 7, 2020, by [[Interscope Records]] and Mogul Vision Music. It was released concurrently with the reissue of his second [[studio album]] ''[[Certified Hitmaker]]'' (2019), which the single appears on.<ref>https://listen.tidal.com/album/131891266/credits</ref>\n\n==Background==\nIn late 2019, a leaked upload of the track on [[Spotify]] reached 21 million streams before it was taken down.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-features/lil-mosey-blueberry-faygo-945083/|title='We Can't Stop These Kids At All': The Curious Case of a Leaked Hit|last=Leight|first=Elias|date=2020-02-04|website=[[Rolling Stone]]|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> It was followed by numerous others, causing the song to go viral before it was officially released on February 7, 2020.<ref name=\"DX\">{{Cite web|url=https://hiphopdx.com/news/id.54469/title.lil-mosey-gets-a-head-start-on-summer-2020-with-blueberry-faygo-single|title=Lil Mosey Gets A Head Start On Summer 2020 With 'Blueberry Faygo' Single|last=|first=|date=2020-02-08|website=[[HipHopDX]]|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> It became Lil Mosey's most successful single to date after being picked up by [[TikTok]] users for dance challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elitedaily.com/p/12-viral-tiktok-songs-youll-never-ever-get-sick-of-listening-to-22414496|title=12 Songs That Went Viral On TikTok, Because They Never, Ever Get Old|website=[[Elite Daily]]|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>\n\n\"Blueberry Faygo\" was produced by Callan and samples \"[[My, My, My (Johnny Gill song)|My, My, My]]\" by American singer-songwriter [[Johnny Gill]].<ref name=\"DX\" />\n\n==Music video==\nThe song's official music video was released on March 26, 2020.<ref>{{Citation|title=Lil Mosey - Blueberry Faygo (Dir. by @_ColeBennett_)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V_jHc_n0p9c|language=en|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref> It was released through music video director, [[Cole Bennett]]'s YouTube channel. The video features appearances from Australian rapper [[The Kid Laroi]] and [[TikTok]] stars [[Addison Rae]] & Lil Huddy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/hip-hop/9343752/lil-mosey-blueberry-faygo-video|title=Lil Mosey&#39;s &#39;Blueberry Faygo&#39; Video: Watch|date=2020-03-26|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-03-26}}</ref>\nThe music video was filmed at the Hype House, a TikTok mansion in Los Angeles.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2020/03/lil-mosey-blueberry-faygo|title=Watch Lil Mosey's \"Blueberry Faygo\" Video|website=Complex|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Blueberry Faygo\" debuted at number 62 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], tying with Mosey's previous single \"[[Stuck in a Dream]]\", his highest-charting single before.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/lyrics/8551828/lil-mosey-blueberry-faygo-lyrics|title=Lil Mosey's 'Blueberry Faygo' Lyrics|date=2020-02-24|website=Billboard|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> It later surpassed \"Stuck in a Dream\", peaking at number 18, becoming Mosey's first top 20. \n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=April 13, 2020|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| 17\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|37|artist=Lil Mosey|song=Blueberry Faygo|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders Tip|2|artist=Lil Mosey|song=Blueberry Faygo|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|11|artist=Lil Mosey|song=Blueberry Faygo|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 17, 2